Color. White to transparent, some areas with scattered orange dots, especially on the carapace and chelipeds (
Fig. 1
). Silvery iridescence is very distinct on the posterolateral junction of the carapace, protruding edges of the first two abdominal somites, upper surface of the movable finger, carina on the outer side and upper spines of the palm and the spine on the outer wrist.
